[p 
	"- ROUTE PLANNING:
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]p
[hr 
]hr
[p 
	"Go to Dungeon 1, get the axe, 92 horns and kill the boss to obtain the orange crystal. Go out to the South to get a hearth then go West, take the golden apple, continue to West to arrive at a window where is a hidden trader. Kill all the enemies to discover the secret basement and get some horns to possess a maximum of 80. Meet the trader to obtain 2 keys.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Back in the plains, go North in the desert zone to access Dungeon 3.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"In this maze, recover 4 keys, 50 horns, "The Magic Rope" and kill the boss to obtain the green crystal.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Once outside, return in plains to go to Dungeon 2.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Recover 1 key, 22 horns, and the yellow crystal by killing the boss, then go outside. Go South to meet Gillian and trade the golden apple to "The Thunder Magic scroll" then go North to meet Battler. On the way, recover 11 horns, for a total of 50 that will allow to buy "The Earth Magic scroll".
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Go North-West, get the Long Sword then go to the top of the map to enter Dungeon 4.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Recover 4 keys , the canoe then kill the boss to obtain the blue crystal. Back outside, go to Dungeon 5 to get the "Speed Shoes", 3 keys the green crystal and 20 horns.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"This dungeon is a crossroads allowing to access the 2nd part of the map, once this one done.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"In this 2nd part, go South and discover a savepoint under a tomb (a death is so fast arrived).
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Continue North to find Dungeon 7.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Kill the middle boss and get the "Ship", then kill the boss to obtain the grey crystal.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Once outside, go South to meet a coyote who, for 10 horns, will allow you to travel an inaccessible part of the map that leads to Dungeon 8.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Inside, kill the middle boss, get the "Thieth's key" and defeat the boss to obtain the blue crystal. Go outside to return to the savepoint and enter Dungeon 6. Kill the boss to get the grey crystal then take the "Ice Bell" before leaving.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Go to Dungeon 7 located in the North, kill the middle boss and the boss to finally obtain the red crystal, which allows to reach the last dungeon, guarded by the terrible Death Adder.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"In this once, kill 2 middle bosses to get the "Golden Axe" and then exchange Mr. Adder's life for peace in Princess Tyris' kingdom.
	$LF
]p
[hr 
]hr
[p 
	"- Bosses explainations
	$LF
]p
[hr 
]hr
[p 
	"- Dungeon 1, green soldier:
	[br 
	]br
	" you just need to manipulate its behavior to get him down and avoid him to attack under his protective sphere, which makes him invinsible for many frames.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"- Dungeon 3, red soldier:
	[br 
	]br
	" same thing as the 1st boss.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"- Dungeon 2, green dragon:
	[br 
	]br
	" we only can dodge his fireballs on the lower part of the blocks that protect him, so just manipulate its behavior to make him not attack on the upper part.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"- Dungeon 4, green wizard:
	[br 
	]br
	" this boss is the most RNG of the game, that force to manipulate luck to make him respawn as soon as possible on the screen. We can't attack him when entering the room, he must disappear once, then we can hit him a time everytime he appears.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"- Dungeon 5, fire skull:
	[br 
	]br
	" normallly, we must start by removing his eight fireballs that turns around him, to be able to hit him. But with a frame-perfect hit using "The Earth Magic scroll", we can deal 4 damages whilst freezing his fireballs on-site, that make gain a hit and 34 frames of invulnerability. His behavior his manipulable to make him stay at the bottom of the screen and not go lower than he does in this TAS.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"- Dungeon 7, green crazy flame:
	[br 
	]br
	" RNG boss where I manipulate his behavior to make him appear in the wished flame. After hitting him, you need to wait 92 frames to hit him again.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"- Dungeon 8, red wizard:
	[br 
	]br
	" same thing as the 4th boss, with an attack furthermore when he disappears.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"- Dungeon 6, red dragon:
	[br 
	]br
	" same as the 2nd boss, with an attack furthermore taht allow him to launch 5 fireballs instead of 3.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"- Dungeon 9, false Death Adder:
	[br 
	]br
	" launch 2 axes per attack. I use this glitch just to show that it's possible to wait at the entrance where he can't reach us.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"- Dungeon 10, Death Adder:
	[br 
	]br
	" same as the last one, with the particularity to be able to launch 3 axes and a power of explosion on the ground. I kill him at a very precise position, so that the hero doesn't have to move by himself to launch the final scene. I think he walked enough.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]p
